**.hsplus for database operations:**
```hsplus
// database.hsplus - Actual queries and operations
import { Database, Query } from "@holoscript/db";
import type { User, Character, Guild } from "./schema-types";

const db = new Database(process.env.DATABASE_URL);

export class CharacterRepository {

  async findByUserId(userId: string): Promise<Character[]> {
    return db.query<Character>
      .select("*")
      .from("characters")
      .where("user_id", "=", userId)
      .orderBy("level", "desc")
      .execute();
  }

  async create(userId: string, data: CreateCharacterInput): Promise<Character> {
    // Validate class choice
    const existingClasses = await db.query<{class: string}>
      .select("class")
      .from("characters")
      .where("user_id", "=", userId)
      .execute();

    if (existingClasses.some(c => c.class === data.class)) {
      throw new Error("You already have a character of this class");
    }

    // Complex initialization
    const stats = this.calculateStartingStats(data.class);
    const inventory = this.getStartingInventory(data.class);

    return db.insert("characters", {
      id: crypto.randomUUID(),
      user_id: userId,
      name: data.name,
      class: data.class,
      stats: JSON.stringify(stats),
      inventory: JSON.stringify(inventory),
      position: JSON.stringify({ x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, world: "starting_zone" })
    });
  }

  async levelUp(characterId: string): Promise<void> {
    const char = await this.findById(characterId);
    if (!char) throw new Error("Character not found");

    const stats = JSON.parse(char.stats);
    const newStats = this.calculateLevelUpStats(char.class, char.level, stats);

    await db.update("characters")
      .set({
        level: char.level + 1,
        stats: JSON.stringify(newStats)
      })
      .where("id", "=", characterId)
      .execute();
  }

  private calculateStartingStats(charClass: string): Stats {
    // Complex class-specific calculations
    switch (charClass) {
      case "warrior":
        return { strength: 15, vitality: 12, intelligence: 5, agility: 8 };
      case "mage":
        return { strength: 5, vitality: 8, intelligence: 15, agility: 10 };
      case "rogue":
        return { strength: 10, vitality: 8, intelligence: 8, agility: 15 };
    }
  }
}
```

**The workflow:**
```
1. Define schema in .holo (visual, easy to review)
         ↓
2. Generate types from .holo → TypeScript interfaces
         ↓
3. Generate migrations from .holo → SQL files
         ↓
4. Write operations in .hsplus (complex queries, business logic)
```

**Tools that work with this:**
```bash
# Generate TypeScript types from schema
holoscript schema:types database-schema.holo -o schema-types.ts

# Generate SQL migrations
holoscript schema:migrate database-schema.holo -o migrations/

# Visualize schema
holoscript schema:diagram database-schema.holo
```

**.holo defines STRUCTURE, .hsplus defines BEHAVIOR.**

Great question! Sometimes code in .hsplus should be pulled out into .holo for clarity.

**Signs you should refactor to .holo:**
1. Large object literal definitions
2. Configuration that rarely changes
3. Scene/world layout code
4. Data that AI agents need to modify

